Five Nigerian students of CEDEC International Secondary School in Lagos will be presented with British International Education Association (BIEA) Award in London today (Tuesday). The award followed the teenagersâ€™ success in the Youth Innovation Competition aimed at engaging young students in Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics (STEM) which took place in London in July this year. The students, three boys and two girls aged 15-17 years bagged the Best Participation Award with their conservation and drone project which focused on using drones to protect the African wild dog and other endanger animals in the continent. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY Students from 34 countries took part in the competition which is sponsored by BIEA, and supported by Born Free Foundation, United Kingdom. Sokoto female student wins best speaker award Winners of 10th Korea-Nigeria drawing competition emerge 13-year-old student wins Mathematics competition in Kwali